PRO TIP: @apply is an anti-pattern in Tailwind v4. Yes, it still works. No, you shouldn't use it.

@apply takes utility classes and converts them back into regular CSS. You're literally undoing the entire point of utilities — co-location with markup.

If you need reusable styles, extract a component. If you need a one-off override, write vanilla CSS. @apply is the worst of both worlds: you lose the readability of utilities AND the power of the cascade.

code:
/* Don't do this */
.btn-primary {
  @apply bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg
    hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors;
}

/* Do this instead — extract a component */
/* Button.tsx */
<button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2
  rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors">
  {children}
</button>

/* Or write actual CSS if you need the cascade */
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--color-primary);
  color: white;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
}

/* Give elements a shared transition name */
.product-image {
  view-transition-name: product-hero;
}

/* Customize the transition animation */
::view-transition-old(product-hero) {
  animation: fade-out 0.3s ease-out;
}

::view-transition-new(product-hero) {
  animation: fade-in 0.3s ease-in;
}

/* Or let the browser handle it — just morph */
::view-transition-group(product-hero) {
  animation-duration: 0.4s;
}

@keyframes slide-in {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(-50px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
}

.element {
  animation: slide-in 0.5s ease-out;
}

/* SLOW — triggers layout every frame */
.element {
  transition: left 0.3s, width 0.3s;
}
.element:hover {
  left: 100px;
  width: 200px;
}

/* FAST — compositor only, GPU-accelerated */
.element {
  transition: transform 0.3s;
}
.element:hover {
  transform: translateX(100px) scaleX(1.5);
}

/* Both look the same to the user.
   One runs at 60fps. One might not. */

/* Full animation for users who want it */
.card {
  animation: slide-in 0.5s ease-out both;
}

/* Reduced motion: instant appearance, no movement */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .card {
    animation: fade-in 0.2s ease-out both;
  }
}

/* Nuclear option: disable ALL animations site-wide */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}

/* scroll() — progress bar that fills as you scroll the page */
.progress-bar {
  animation: fill linear;
  animation-timeline: scroll();
}
@keyframes fill {
  to { width: 100%; }
}

/* view() — element fades in when it enters viewport */
.section {
  animation: reveal linear both;
  animation-timeline: view();
  animation-range: entry 0% entry 100%;
